nd questions, and he raises our awareness of the things we don’t yet know and why we really should. Using the latest scientific findings, The Birds at My Table takes a global swoop from 30,000 feet down to the backyard bird feeder and pushes our understanding of the many aspects of bird feeding back up to new heights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aBirdsxEffect of human beings on. 0aBirdsxFeeding and feeds. 0aHuman-animal relationships. 4aGeneral Science. 4aNature Guides & Natural History. 4aOrnithology. 7aNATURE / Animals / Birds.2bisacsh  agarden birds, urban ecology, supplementary feeding, nature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR Single-User eBook-Package 2018z978311070864608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501710797zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501710797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501710797/original  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-070864-6  COR Single-User eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles